1. Definition:
- Git is a Version Control System (VCS).
2. Type of git:
- Local VCS: server & client on same hardware.
- Central VCS: have a central VCS which is connecting to one or more clients.
- Distributed VCS: mutliple VCS and sync among each others. 
3. Git status:
- modified: file has been changed but not having saved in local DB.
- staged: file marked as modified & will be save in next commit submission.
- commited: all changes have been saved into local database.
4. Directory:
- Working directory: contain a version of project
- Staging directory: is a file in Git folder which contain information will be
  commited.
- Git directory: where git save database of metadata.

(*) Reference:
- https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup
